Richard Atwell sends:

> What's the best way to deal with rust holes in the battery trays?  I see
> there are replacement panels available but I have no idea how much work is
> involved in fitting them.

You cut out the old ones completely and weld in new ones. Easy job if you
have a die grinder, angle grinder and MIG welder.
